    {
      "question": "If the polynomial $p(x) = x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10$ is divided by $g(x) = x^2 - 2x + k$, the remainder is found to be $x + a$. What is the value of $k$?",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Perform polynomial long division of $p(x)$ by $g(x)$.",
          "The division of $x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10$ by $x^2 - 2x + k$ yields a quotient $x^2 - 4x + (8-k)$.",
          "The remainder obtained is $(2k-16+25)x + (10 - k(8-k))$.",
          "Equate the remainder to $x + a$. The coefficient of $x$ must be $1$, so $2k - 16 + 25 = 1$.",
          "Solve $2k + 9 = 1 \\Rightarrow 2k = -8 \\Rightarrow k = -4$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^4 - 6x^3 + 16x^2 - 25x + 10 = (x^2 - 2x + k)(x^2 - 4x + 8 - k) + (2k - 16 + 25)x + (10 - k(8-k)) \\\\ 2k + 9 = 1 \\\\ 2k = -8 \\\\ k = -4$"
      },
      "topic": "Polynomials",
      "subtopic": "division algorithm for polynomials",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
